 <!-- This is a DTD for data acceptable for processing by the ISI 
      Links system.  The top level element is ArticleSet.  Note that 
      the following data is obligatory for all items, both source 
      items and reference items: 
      Last name of first author 
      Volume number 
      First page 
      Publication year 
      Journal Title 
      The character set is 7 bit ascii, with non-roman and accented 
      characters normalized to ascii. ISO Latin 1 entities, as would be 
      found through 
      <!ENTITY % ISOlat1  PUBLIC "ISO 8879-1986//ENTITIES Added 
      Latin 1//EN"> 
      are acceptable. 
   --> 
 
 <!ELEMENT ArticleSet     - - (Article+)> 
 <!ELEMENT Article        - - (PublisherId, ArticleId, Journal, ArticleTitle, 
                               FirstPage, LastPage, AuthorList,                         					 ReferenceList? )> 
 
 <!ELEMENT Journal        - - (PublisherName, JournalTitle, Issn?, 
                            Volume, Issue?, PubDate )> 
 <!ELEMENT PublisherId    - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT ArticleId      - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!-- -------------------------------------------------------- 
                Conditions on the ArticleId element 
 
 1) For outbound (from ISI) links: the ArticleId must contain sufficient 
    information so that a URL to the target of the links can be 
    generated, given a base URL and URL pattern.  For example, if the 
    base URL is http://domain.com/cgi-bin/linkserv.pl  and the URL 
    pattern is  issn=<issn>&vol=<vol>&iss=<issue>&page=<bp> then an 
    ArticleId like this is acceptable: 1234-5678_v21_i003_123; the 
    corresponding generated URL is 
 
 http://domain.com/cgi-bin/linkserv.pl?issn=1234-5678&vol=v23&iss=i003&pa 
 ge=123 
    Subfields in the ArticleId are separated by "_" characters; not all 
    subfields in the ArticleId need be present in the URL 
    pattern. Static pages can also be accomodated thus: 
         http://domain.com/1234-5678/v21/i003/123.html 
    with a pattern like <issn>/<vol>/<issue>/<bp>.html. 
    Alternatively, a monolithic ArticleId without underscores like 
    123abc456def789 is acceptible, if it can be plugged into one spot in 
    the URL pattern, e.g. 
         http://domain.com/cgi-bin/axs.pl?type=link&id=123abc456def789 
 
 2) For inbound (to ISI) links: The format is arbitrary.  The ArticleId 
    is used for communication with the data supplier.  For simple 
    inbound links, ISI supplies a list of ArticleIds, of the "hot" 
    (i.e. present in the ISI databases) articles.  For inbound links 
    with additional content (e.g. "times cited") additional information 
    is supplied with the ArticleId. DOI, SICI, or other types of 
    identifier are commonly used. 
 
 3) A data supplier may desire both inbound and outbound links; the 
    format/use requirements of 1) must be met. 
 
 4) Article identifiers must be unique for a given data supplier, across 
    the database.  The data supplier must check this; ISI will not, and 
    if more than one record is given with the same ArticleId, only one 
    (indeterminate) will be used by ISI. 
 
  -------------------------------------------------------- --> 
 
 
 <!ELEMENT PublisherName  - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT JournalTitle   - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT Issn           - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT Volume         - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT Issue          - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT PubDate        - - (Year, Month?, Day?)> 
 <!ELEMENT Year           - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT Month          - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT Day            - - (#PCDATA)> 
 
 <!ELEMENT ArticleTitle   - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT FirstPage      - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT LastPage       - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT AuthorList     - - (Author+)> 
 <!ELEMENT Author         - - (FirstName?, MiddleName?, LastName, 
 Suffix?)> 
 <!ELEMENT FirstName      - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT MiddleName     - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT LastName       - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT Suffix         - - (#PCDATA)> 
 
 <!ELEMENT ReferenceList         - - (Reference+)> 
 <!ELEMENT Reference             - - (ReferenceJournal, ReferenceYear, 
                                   ReferenceVolume, 
 ReferenceFirstPage, 
                                   ReferenceAuthor,  ReferenceId)> 
 <!ELEMENT ReferenceJournal      - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT ReferenceYear         - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT ReferenceVolume       - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!ELEMENT ReferenceFirstPage    - - (#PCDATA)> 
 <!-- A previous version of this DTD allowed arbitrary #PCDATA in 
      a ReferenceAuthor element.  Since this was ambiguous, it has been 
      replaced with a parsed out Authorlist element (which also allows 
      multiple authors. --> 
 <!ELEMENT ReferenceAuthor       - - (AuthorList)> 
 <!ELEMENT ReferenceId           - - (#PCDATA)> 
 
